title: Letterhead, Bick & Schatel,  Cleveland, late 20th century
medium: Letterpress: gray ink on light cream wove paper
markings: Watermark: Beaver Bond / (crouching beaver facing left)/ Rag Content
inscribed: Across top right of sheet in gray: BICK & SCHATEL / 10510 PARK LANE / CLEVELAND 6, OHIO /795-6377".  Across bottom of sheet, in gray, "MEMBERS OF AMERICAN INSTITUTE OF CERTIFIED PUBLIC ACCOUNTANTS / OHIO SOCIETY OF CERTIFIED PUBLIC ACCOUNTANTS
description: Company name  and address in gray ink at upper center with additional text across bottom.    At upper right, embossed grid of numbers: row of  9 ones at top, followed by row of twos, threes, fours, fives, sixes, sevens, eights, nines above a ruled line; beneath line is phrase "CERTIFIED PUBLIC ACCOUNTANS" serving as the total.

tombstone.epitaph:
Letterhead, Bick & Schatel,  Cleveland, late 20th century. Letterpress: gray ink on light cream wove paper. 
Gift of Thomas F. O'Malley. 1999-59-3
